 Purpose:
Reverse proxy and web server providing hostname-based routing to all web services. Routes traffic from clean URLs (git.lab.local, blog.lab.local) to backend Docker containers.

Access Information:
- URL: http://apps.lab.local & http://mntr.lab.local
- Port(s): 80 (HTTP), 443 (HTTPS)
- Location (VM): apps.lab.local mntr.lab.local
- Container/Service Name: nginx

Credentials:
- Admin Username: N/A (no authentication - routing only)
- Admin Password Location: N/A

Technical Details:
- Database: None
- Configuration Files: /opt/docker/nginx/nginx.conf
- Data Location: /opt/docker/nginx/html/ (static files/landing page)
- Log Location: docker logs nginx

Common Operations:

Restart:
docker compose restart nginx

View Logs:
docker logs nginx -f

Check Status:
docker ps | grep nginx
curl -I http://localhost

Backup:
tar -czf /opt/backups/nginx-$(date +%Y%m%d).tar.gz /opt/docker/nginx/

Dependencies:
- Requires: FreeIPA DNS (for hostname resolution)
- Required by: All web services & monitoring (Gitea, WordPress, Grafana, Portainer, DokuWiki, Uptime Kuma)(Grafana, Prometheus, & Loki)

Notes:
- All service routes are defined in nginx.conf server blocks
- Restart Nginx after adding/modifying routes
- Test config before restart: docker exec nginx nginx -t
